Package boundary

Class HDBManagerMenu

java.lang.Object
boundary.HDBManagerMenu
public class HDBManagerMenu extends Object
The HDBManagerMenu class provides the user interface for HDB manager users.

This boundary class:

  • Facilitates BTO project creation and management
  • Allows managers to process applications and withdrawal requests
  • Enables responding to user enquiries about projects
  • Provides tools for approving HDB officer registrations
  • Generates various reports on applications and project status
Version:
1.0

    • createNewProject

      private void createNewProject()
      Creates a new BTO project with user-specified details. This method:
      • Validates project name for uniqueness and format
      • Collects project location and flat unit allocations
      • Sets application open/close dates with validation
      • Configures officer slots and auto-publish settings
      • Adds the project to the system if it doesn't overlap with existing projects

    • deleteProject

      private void deleteProject(BTOProject project)
      Handles the deletion of a BTO project with various safety checks. This method:
      • Validates that the project is eligible for deletion based on its status
      • Prevents deletion of projects that are currently open for applications
      • Provides warnings about existing applications that might be affected
      • Requires password confirmation for security
      • Removes the project from the system if all validations pass
      Parameters:
      project - The BTO project to delete

    • editProjectDates

      private void editProjectDates(BTOProject project)
      Allows editing of project application dates with appropriate constraints. This method:
      • Applies different rules for projects with existing applications
      • For projects with applications, only allows modifying the closing date
      • For new projects, allows changing both opening and closing dates
      • Validates that dates are in the future and properly ordered
      • Updates the project and persists changes to the database
      Parameters:
      project - The BTO project whose dates need to be edited

    • processApplicationStatus

      private void processApplicationStatus(List<BTOApplication> applications, BTOProject project)
      Processes application status changes for a selected BTO application. This method:
      • Allows managers to change application status between PENDING, SUCCESSFUL, and UNSUCCESSFUL
      • Handles different status transitions based on the current application state
      • Enforces business rules around what status transitions are permitted
      • Updates the application database after status changes
      Parameters:
      applications - List of applications to choose from
      project - The BTO project these applications belong to

    • processWithdrawalRequests

      private void processWithdrawalRequests(List<BTOApplication> applications, BTOProject project)
      Processes withdrawal requests for BTO applications. This method:
      • Filters applications to display only those with pending withdrawal requests
      • Provides options to approve or reject each withdrawal request
      • Handles special logic for BOOKED applications (returning units to the available pool)
      • Updates application status and project inventory after processing
      Parameters:
      applications - List of all applications for the project
      project - The BTO project these applications belong to

    • manageOfficerRegistrations

      private void manageOfficerRegistrations()
      Manages the approval or rejection of HDB officer registrations for projects. This method:
      • Displays projects with their officer assignment status
      • Shows pending officer registrations for a selected project
      • Provides options to approve or reject each officer request
      • Updates officer assignment and project data after processing

    • generateReports

      private void generateReports()
      Displays a menu of available reports and generates the selected report. This method:
      • Shows a list of the manager's projects to select from
      • Offers different report types (all applications, successful applications, etc.)
      • Generates the selected report based on project application data
      • Provides an option to save the report to a file

    • saveReportToFile

      private void saveReportToFile(String filename)
      Saves the most recently generated report to a file. This method:
      • Temporarily redirects System.out to capture the report output
      • Re-runs the last report to capture its content
      • Writes the captured content to the specified file
      • Creates any necessary parent directories for the output file
      Parameters:
      filename - The path where the report should be saved

    • executeLastReport

      private void executeLastReport()
      Re-executes the last generated report. This method:
      • Checks if report data is available from the previous report generation
      • Calls the appropriate report generation method based on the last report type
      • Used primarily when saving reports to files
